text: Jaime Herrera Beutler (born November 3, 1978) is an American politician. She is a member of the Republican Party. She was a representative for Washington in the United States House of Representatives from 2011 to 2023. Jaime Herrera Beutler with nine other members of the Republican party and all of the Democrats voted to impeach Donald Trump a second time. In August 2022, Herrera Beutler lost the Republican nomination in her re-election campaign against Trump-supported primary challenger Joe Kent. ==References== Category:1978 births Category:Living people Category:American Christians Category:United States representatives from Washington Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians Category:Politicians from Glendale, California
